					<div id=3D"mw-content-text" class=3D"mw-body-content"><div class=3D"mw=
-content-ltr mw-parser-output" lang=3D"en" dir=3D"ltr"><div class=3D"shortd=
escription nomobile noexcerpt noprint searchaux" style=3D"display:none">In =
mathematics, invariant of square matrices</div>
<div role=3D"note" class=3D"hatnote navigation-not-searchable">This article=
 is about mathematics. For determinants in epidemiology, see <a href=3D"htt=
ps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Risk_factor" title=3D"Risk factor">Risk factor</=
a>. For determinants in immunology, see <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org=
/wiki/Epitope" title=3D"Epitope">Epitope</a>.</div>
<link rel=3D"mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href=3D"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r=
1320445320"><div role=3D"note" class=3D"hatnote navigation-not-searchable">=
Not to be confused with <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Discrimina=
nt" title=3D"Discriminant">Discriminant</a>.</div>
<p>In <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mathematics" title=3D"Mathem=
atics">mathematics</a>, the <b>determinant</b> is a <a href=3D"https://en.w=
ikipedia.org/wiki/Scalar_(mathematics)" title=3D"Scalar (mathematics)">scal=
ar</a>-valued <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Function_(mathematic=
s)" title=3D"Function (mathematics)">function</a> of the entries of a <a hr=
ef=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Square_matrix" title=3D"Square matrix">=
square matrix</a>. The determinant of a matrix <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>A=
</i></span> is commonly denoted <span class=3D"texhtml">det(<i>A</i>)</span=
>, <span class=3D"texhtml">det <i>A</i></span>, or <span class=3D"texhtml">=
|<span class=3D"nowrap" style=3D"padding-left:0.1em; padding-right:0.1em;">=
<i>A</i></span>|</span>. Its value characterizes some properties of the mat=
rix and the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Linear_map" title=3D"L=
inear map">linear map</a> represented, on a given <a href=3D"https://en.wik=
ipedia.org/wiki/Basis_(linear_algebra)" title=3D"Basis (linear algebra)">ba=
sis</a>, by the matrix. In particular, the determinant is nonzero <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/If_and_only_if" title=3D"If and only if">=
if and only if</a> the matrix is <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/I=
nvertible_matrix" title=3D"Invertible matrix">invertible</a> and the corres=
ponding linear map is an <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Linear_is=
omorphism" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Linear isomorphism">isomorphism</=
a>. However, if the determinant is zero, the matrix is referred to as singu=
lar, meaning it does not have an inverse.
</p><p>The determinant is completely determined by the two following proper=
ties: the determinant of a product of matrices is the product of their dete=
rminants, and the determinant of a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki=
/Triangular_matrix" title=3D"Triangular matrix">triangular matrix</a> is th=
e product of its diagonal entries.
</p><p>The determinant of a <span class=3D"texhtml">2 =C3=97 2</span> matri=
x is
