    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle 2\times 2}</a=
nnotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/f8a0e3400ffb97d67c00267ed50cddfe824cbe80" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.338ex; width:5.165ex; height:2.176ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle 2\t=
imes 2}"></span>-matrices, and that continue to hold for determinants of la=
rger matrices. They are as follows:<sup id=3D"cite_ref-1" class=3D"referenc=
e"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Determinant#cite_note-1"><span =
class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>1<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></=
sup> first, the determinant of the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki=
/Identity_matrix" title=3D"Identity matrix">identity matrix</a> <span class=
