<p>The <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rule_of_Sarrus" title=3D"Ru=
le of Sarrus">rule of Sarrus</a> is a mnemonic for the expanded form of thi=
s determinant: the sum of the products of three diagonal north-west to sout=
h-east lines of matrix elements, minus the sum of the products of three dia=
gonal south-west to north-east lines of elements, when the copies of the fi=
rst two columns of the matrix are written beside it as in the illustration.=
 This scheme for calculating the determinant of a <span class=3D"texhtml">3=
 =C3=97 3</span> matrix does not carry over into higher dimensions.
</p>
