er's determinant theorem</a> states that for <i>A</i>, an <span class=3D"te=
xhtml"><i>m</i> =C3=97 <i>n</i></span> matrix, and <i>B</i>, an <span class=
=3D"texhtml"><i>n</i> =C3=97 <i>m</i></span> matrix (so that <i>A</i> and <=
i>B</i> have dimensions allowing them to be multiplied in either order form=
ing a square matrix):
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e \det \left(I_{\mathit {m}}+AB\right)=3D\det \left(I_{\mathit {n}}+BA\righ=
t),}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mo movablelimits=3D"true" form=3D"prefix">det</mo>
        <mrow>
          <mo>(</mo>
          <mrow>
            <msub>
              <mi>I</mi>
              <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                  <mi class=3D"MJX-tex-mathit" mathvariant=3D"italic">m</mi=
>
                </mrow>
              </mrow>
            </msub>
            <mo>+</mo>
            <mi>A</mi>
            <mi>B</mi>
          </mrow>
          <mo>)</mo>
        </mrow>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mo movablelimits=3D"true" form=3D"prefix">det</mo>
        <mrow>
          <mo>(</mo>
          <mrow>
            <msub>
              <mi>I</mi>
              <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                  <mi class=3D"MJX-tex-mathit" mathvariant=3D"italic">n</mi=
>
                </mrow>
              </mrow>
            </msub>
            <mo>+</mo>
            <mi>B</mi>
            <mi>A</mi>
          </mrow>
          <mo>)</mo>
        </mrow>
        <mo>,</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \det \left(I_=
{\mathit {m}}+AB\right)=3D\det \left(I_{\mathit {n}}+BA\right),}</annotatio=
n>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/0a0bfc460f0a39f8891b5eca2c29f4b526e5e3ee" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
