et \left(I_{\mathit {m}}+AB\right)=3D\det \left(I_{\mathit {n}}+BA\right),}=
"></span></dd></dl>
<p>where <i>I</i><sub><i>m</i></sub> and <i>I</i><sub><i>n</i></sub> are th=
e <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>m</i> =C3=97 <i>m</i></span> and <span class=
=3D"texhtml"><i>n</i> =C3=97 <i>n</i></span> identity matrices, respectivel=
y.
</p><p>From this general result several consequences follow.
</p>
