<p>These inequalities can be proved by expressing the traces and the determ=
inant in terms of the eigenvalues. As such, they represent the well-known f=
act that the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Harmonic_mean" title=
=3D"Harmonic mean">harmonic mean</a> is less than the <a href=3D"https://en=
.wikipedia.org/wiki/Geometric_mean" title=3D"Geometric mean">geometric mean=
</a>, which is less than the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arith=
metic_mean" title=3D"Arithmetic mean">arithmetic mean</a>, which is, in tur=
n, less than the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Root_mean_square"=
