rminant_lemma" title=3D"Matrix determinant lemma">matrix determinant lemma<=
/a> allows rapid calculation of the determinant of <span class=3D"texhtml">=
<i>A</i> + <i>uv</i><sup>T</sup></span>, where <i>u</i> and <i>v</i> are co=
lumn vectors.
</p><p>Charles Dodgson (i.e. <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lewis=
_Carroll" title=3D"Lewis Carroll">Lewis Carroll</a> of <i><a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alice%27s_Adventures_in_Wonderland" title=3D"Alice'=
s Adventures in Wonderland">Alice's Adventures in Wonderland</a></i> fame) =
invented a method for computing determinants called <a href=3D"https://en.w=
ikipedia.org/wiki/Dodgson_condensation" title=3D"Dodgson condensation">Dodg=
son condensation</a>.  This method does not always work in its original for=
m.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-58" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikiped=
ia.org/wiki/Determinant#cite_note-58"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>=
